<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1884-08-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1884-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="179" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d179">
                        <head>No. 179.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">West</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1884-08-22"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 22,
                                1884</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note of the 11th
                            instant, I have the honor to inform you that the memorandum which
                            accompanied it, concerning the state of the labor traffic in the Western
                            Pacific islands, has received careful examination. This Government looks
                            with favor upon any humanitarian work, and would like more information
                            as to the scope and form of the proposed agreement.</p>
                        <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>